<TITLE> Bush to speak about Iraq on Thursday: CNN </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, April 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - President George W Bush plans to address the nation on Thursday morning about the Iraq war, CNN reported on Sunday. In a report on its Web site citing sources in the Bush administration and Congress, the cable network said Bush is expected to discuss the decision to reduce combat tours of duty to 12 months from 15 months. Asked about the CNN report, White House spokeswoman Dana Perino said aboard Air Force One: "We don't have anything to announce yet. I wouldn't be surprised if he has something to say about Iraq this week." Bush was on board the presidential plane heading back to Washington from a US-Russia summit. The address would follow two days of testimony before Congress by Gen. David Petraeus, the top US commander in Iraq, and US Ambassador to Iraq Ryan Crocker. "It will be an update -- having been briefed by Petraeus and Crocker, here's where we are," one Republican official said about the president's speech, CNN reported. Bush is scheduled to leave on Thursday for his Texas ranch for a few days of vacation
